{"BR": {"BR_id": "478", "BR_author": "the-lay", "BRopenT": "2019-10-29T23:18:47Z", "BRcloseT": "2019-11-02T08:52:57Z", "BR_text": {"BRsummary": "Specifying cuda device through SupervisedRunner doesn't get picked up", "BRdescription": "\n When you specify cuda device in SupervisedRunner (and SupervisedWandbRunner), it doesn't influence what GPUs will be used. Manually setting CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES works though.\n Example\n import torch\n from catalyst.dl.runner import SupervisedRunner, SupervisedWandbRunner\n ...\n runner = SupervisedRunner(device=torch.device('cuda:1'))\n runner.train(...)\n Expected behavior: Only GPU with ID 1 should be used.\n Actual behavior: Catalyst uses all available devices.\n \t"}, "comments": {"comments_0": {"comment_id": 1, "comment_author": "the-lay", "commentT": "2019-10-30T12:21:06Z", "comment_text": "\n \t\tThanks, should be fixed in <denchmark-link:https://github.com/catalyst-team/catalyst/pull/482>#482</denchmark-link>\n \n \t\t"}, "comments_1": {"comment_id": 2, "comment_author": "the-lay", "commentT": "2019-11-02T08:52:57Z", "comment_text": "\n \t\tFixed\n \t\t"}}}, "commit": {"commit_id": "d629b26fa52b7442c433aadc72a47a109e0dd6d6", "commit_author": "Roman Tezikov", "commitT": "2019-11-02 11:52:26+03:00", "changed_files": {"file_0": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 0, "file_old_name": "catalyst\\dl\\core\\runner.py", "file_new_name": "catalyst\\dl\\core\\runner.py", "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 0, "added_lines": "62,63", "deleted_lines": "62"}}}, "file_1": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 2, "file_old_name": "catalyst\\dl\\utils\\torch.py", "file_new_name": "catalyst\\dl\\utils\\torch.py", "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 1, "added_lines": "23", "deleted_lines": "23", "method_info": {"method_name": "process_components", "method_params": "_Model,_Criterion,_Optimizer,_Scheduler,Dict", "method_startline": "18", "method_endline": "23"}}, "hunk_1": {"Ismethod": 1, "added_lines": "23,24", "deleted_lines":